# Staging-only deploy workflow

**Never push, merge, or deploy to production unless the user explicitly says yes to "push to production".**

## Default behavior (always)

1. Make code changes on the **`staging`** branch (or commit there).
2. **Only** `git push origin staging` — triggers `flightslate-staging` on Railway.
3. After deploy, tell the user: **"Live on staging: https://flightslate-staging-production.up.railway.app"** and ask: **"Do you want me to push to production?"**
4. Wait for explicit **yes** before any of:
   - `git push origin main`
   - merge `staging` → `main`
   - production Railway redeploy
   - production env var changes

## Forbidden without explicit approval

- Pushing to `main`
- Merging to `main`
- Redeploying `flightslate-web`
- Changing production `DATABASE_URL` or production Railway vars

## Staging URLs

- Railway: https://flightslate-staging-production.up.railway.app
- Custom (when DNS set): https://staging.newtechaviation.com

## Production (do not touch unless approved)

- Branch: `main` → service `flightslate-web` → www.newtechaviation.com
